Project description =
The Chicago Weather App that I made was made with java. It basically shows weather information for Chicago city using data from the National 
Weather Service which is an API. The app has two screens. The first screen basically shows today’s weather, including the temperature, a short 
description like if its sunny or cloudy), and the chance of rain. The second screen would be a 3-day forecast of day/night temperatures and wind 
information. This was basically built with JavaFX to create the user interface and Maven to run the program. The weather data comes from an API 
that was already given in the starter code. I also used two design patterns called the Adapter Pattern and Template Method Pattern to help organize 
my code and make it easier to understand. While working on this project, I also made sure the app was easy to use. I also added buttons so users can 
switch between the two screens without any problems. I also added some colors and clear labels so everything is easy to read. For the above and 
beyond, I included the chance of precipitation, which helps users know if it might rain. Overall, this project helped me learn how to 
build a Java app, use an API, and design a simple but useful interface.

-Some technologies that were used were
Java, JavaFX, Maven, and the National Weather Service API

-Some Features=
It Shows today’s weather (temperature + condition), Shows 3-day forecast (day/night temps and wind info), can go to different scenes,
simple and colorful background, and i also added precipitation information

You ran this project by the following=
mvn clean compile exec:java

I learned the following=
JavaFX, How to get data from an API, organizing code using design patterns, fixing code bugs, and how to design a simple and clear interface

